<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="102" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5693</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-07T15:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1543. Inform <persName>Bertron</persName> that his 12, July 2, to Mr.
                                    <persName>McAdoo</persName> has been referred to this Department
                                by President. President approves in principle of educational
                                publicity campaign and authorizes expense $30,000 already incurred.
                                The question of further outlay and a comprehensive plan is receiving
                                the careful attention of the Department which will advise you
                                definitely at an early date.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>